    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Lately a few changes were merged to reduce interdependency (mostly to reduce dependency on libevmasm from within libyul), however there is a PR which does the converse, adds dependency on libyul from libevmasm. That would be the first instance, and it is not merged yet.\r\n\r\nIt seems we cannot remove dependency on libevmasm anytime soon from libyul, so I would argue that making this dependency bidirectional is a bad idea and that this current issue is a bad idea too in the current situation.",
